<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 08 at 7:48AM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Johnston County
through 845 AM EDT...
At 746 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Smithfield, moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Smithfield, Clayton, Benson, Micro, Selma, Four Oaks, Pine Level,
Kenly, Princeton and Emit.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
